==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Attune
<hw>At*tune"</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Attuned</conjf> <pr>(<?/)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Attuning</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Pref. <ets>ad-</ets> +
<ets>tune</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To tune or put in tune; to make melodious; to
adjust, as one sound or musical instrument to another; <as>as, to
<ex>attune</ex> the voice to a harp</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To arrange fitly; to make accordant.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Wake to energy each social aim,⟦br⟧
<qex>Attuned</qex> spontaneous to the will of Jove.</q>
<rj><qau>Beattie.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Atwain</ent>⟦br⟧
